# A heavy isotope of the simplest [[alkali]] [[metal]], (''symbol'' Li) with an [[atomic number]] of 3 and containing 8 neutrons. Metalithium is an artificial isotope produced by bombarding Lithium 7 with neutrons. It is radioactive, with a [[half-life]] of 6.3 seconds.